exercise.name: Jumping Jacks
exercise.description: Jump your feet apart as you reach your arms overhead.  Stay rhythmic

audios.text: Jump your feet apart as you reach your arms overhead.  Stay rhythmic

exercise.name: Dynamic Hamstring Stretch
exercise.description: Plant your heel and trigger your toes up.  Keeping your leg straight and back flat, sweep your arms through.  Switch legs while maintaining smooth form.

audios.text: Plant your heel and trigger your toes up.  Keeping your leg straight and back flat, sweep your arms through.  Switch legs while maintaining smooth form.

exercise.name: Reverse Lunge Reaches
exercise.description: Step back and drop down with your knee hovering just above the ground.  On the side that stepped back, reach your arm up to the ceiling.

audios.text: Step back and drop down with your knee hovering just above the ground.  On the side that stepped back, reach your arm up to the ceiling

exercise.name: Tin Soldiers
exercise.description: Start tall with your feet together.. Kick one leg straight out in front of you,, while keeping your torso tall and both legs straight.. Snap your heel down,, to finish back underneath you.. Alternate legs..

exercise.name: Hip Cradles
exercise.description: Stand tall and gently pull your knee and ankle up toward your chest, stretching the outside of your hip.

audios.text: Stand tall and gently pull your knee and ankle up toward your chest, stretching the outside of your hip.

exercise.name: Arm Circles Forward
exercise.description: Cycle your arms forward in a large circular motion.. Remember to stand tall.

exercise.name: Arm Circles Backward
exercise.description: Stand tall and cycle your arms up and overhead, then back behind you, in a large circular motion.

exercise.name: Bent Over YTW
exercise.description: Hinge over until your upper body is parallel with the ground.  Lift your arms into a Y position and imagine squeezing a pencil between your shoulder blades.  Lower back down and then repeat in a T with arms out to the sides, and finally a W with bent arms.

audios.text: Hinge over until your upper body is parallel with the ground.  Lift your arms into a Y position and imagine squeezing a pencil between your shoulder blades.  Lower back down and then repeat in a T with arms out to the sides, and finally a W with bent arms.

exercise.name: Kneeling Quadriceps Stretch
exercise.description: Kneel on the floor with your right leg forward and left leg back.  With perfect posture, press your hips forward until your feel a stretch in the front of your left thigh.

audios.text: Kneel on the floor with your right leg forward and left leg back.  With perfect posture, press your hips forward until your feel a stretch in the front of your left thigh.
Kneel on the floor with your right leg forward and left leg back.  With perfect posture, press your hips forward until your feel a stretch in the front of your left thigh.

exercise.name: Kneeling Quadriceps Stretch
exercise.description: Kneel on the floor with your left leg forward and right leg back.  With perfect posture, press your hips forward until your feel a stretch in the front of your right thigh.

audios.text: Kneel on the floor with your left leg forward and right leg back.  With perfect posture, press your hips forward until your feel a stretch in the front of your right thigh.

exercise.name: Figure Four Stretch
exercise.description: Put your left ankle against your right knee.  Use both hands to pull your legs back toward you.  Focus on rotating your left knee out to feel a greater stretch on the lateral hip.

audios.text: Put your left ankle against your right knee.  Use both hands to pull your legs back toward you.  Focus on rotating your left knee out to feel a greater stretch on the lateral hip.

exercise.name: Figure Four Stretch
exercise.description: Put your right ankle against your left knee.  Use both hands to pull your legs back toward you.  Focus on rotating your right knee out to feel a greater stretch on the lateral hip.

audios.text: Put your right ankle against your left knee.  Use both hands to pull your legs back toward you.  Focus on rotating your right knee out to feel a greater stretch on the lateral hip.

exercise.name: Lower Back Stretch
exercise.description: Hug your left knee up towards your chest and pull it across your body with your right hand.  As you breathe out let your left arm drape on the floor as your work deeper into the stretch

exercise.name: Floor Slides
exercise.description: Lay on the ground,, with your knees bent and feet flat.. Reach your arms overhead as far as you can,, keeping your elbows, shoulders, and wrists pressed into the ground.. Slide back to repeat..
